If something goes wrong with the simulation closing and it can't restart, try a computer restart, this will undo changes to steering wheel resistance

To launch Simulation, use one of the following trial files:
Trial 1: maunal control, no cones
Trial 2: blended control, .5 weight, no cones, 
Trial 3: maunal control, cones
Trial 4: blended control, .5 weight, cones

Participent data is save in ParticipentData/T#, where # corrispawns to the trial run
Data logs are in the form of P[Participent id]R[Run number]
Participent id is a value asked for after running the trial bash file before the sim launches
Run number is an autoiterating value based on the existing data logs

To change blended control weight during sim, use keypad, the following keys are bound:
0: 0%
1: 25%
2: 50%
3: 75%
4: 100%

To change bindings, go to /home/labstudent/carla/PythonAPI/max_testing/manual_control_steeringwheel.py, search for #Map keypad keys to weight changes, change self.weight = .25 to desired value

Trials are customised using file args

Katie_Logger:
trial (t), integer, trial type, effect: datalog placment
participent id (d), integer, effect: datalog naming
obstacles (o), boolen, obstacle presence, effect: correct tracking of automatic steering

manual_control_steeringwheel:
obstacles (o), boolen, obstacle presence, effect: spawns obstacles, automatic steering around obstacles, default: false
weight (w), float, automatic control weight, effect: percentage of automatic control in blending, 0 for manual control, defaul value: 1

